                    <comment id="12568223" author="mreutegg" created="Tue, 12 Feb 2008 17:12:45 +0000"  >Fixed in revision: 620866</comment>
                    <comment id="12577339" author="mreutegg" created="Tue, 11 Mar 2008 08:54:00 +0000"  >When there are stored fields with significant content (i.e. to support highlighting) resolving the hierarchy in a query is very expensive without this change.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
Merged changes into the 1.4 branch for jackrabbit-core 1.4.2 release.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
svn revision: 635855</comment>
                    <comment id="12578265" author="jukkaz" created="Thu, 13 Mar 2008 12:15:34 +0000"  >How pressing is the need to release this in 1.4.2? AFAIUI this is a performance improvement and as such I&amp;#39;d rather target this for 1.5.</comment>
                    <comment id="12578658" author="mreutegg" created="Fri, 14 Mar 2008 09:12:47 +0000"  >I&amp;#39;d describe it as a performance *fix* ;)&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
If you enable support for highlighting in the query handler and upload documents where text is extracted, the query performance will drop significantly for hierarchy resolution. I&amp;#39;ve seen queries taking 10 or more seconds on a workspace with a reasonable amount of content. With this fix, the time drops to milliseconds.</comment>
